"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62897","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>The UK is committed to the protection of endangered species, including through playing a leading role in the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES). CITES promotes the sustainability of endangered species through either prohibiting trade or strictly controlling any trade through a licensing system. The breeding and ranching of endangered species for commercial gain can be permitted under CITES. The UK fully supports the aims of CITES and works to ensure that assessment of whether trade should be permitted for any particular species is based on robust scientific evidence.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-06-24T15:35:37.7498248Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62897/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62897/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Nature Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what his policy is on the farming of endangered species for commercial gain.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","201502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62898","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>There are no plans to extend eligibility for either of these two schemes. Both of these schemes build on existing EU schemes where the EU rules prevent any changes in eligibility that would allow those flooded before 1 December 2013 to apply.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-26T16:46:42.491452Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62898/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62898/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the contribution by the Prime Minister of 18 June 2014, Official Report, column 1116W, what assessment he has made of the cost of flooding damage to (a) farmers and (b) small businesses from the beginning of the financial year 2013 which will become eligible for support from his Department's (a) Farming Recovery Fund and (b) support for fishermen schemes; and what estimate he has made of the number of additional claims made under each such scheme as a result of this extended eligibility.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","201508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62899","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The Prime Minister in his comments mentioned looking at the eligibility for grants for those who had suffered from the winter flooding to earlier flooding incidents, and we are doing so. The Government has provided a number of funding support mechanisms for those affected by the winter floods. Because of their origin as EU grant schemes, neither of the two grants which are referred to here, the Farming Recovery Fund and the European Fisheries Fund, are open to extending eligibility.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-06-30T16:00:27.029186Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62899/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62899/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the contribution by the Prime Minister of 18 June 2014, Official Report, column 1116W, what extra resource his Department will provide to deal with extended eligibility for claims made under the (a) Farming Recovery Fund and (b) support for fishermen schemes.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","201507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62900","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>Defra, Natural England and the Animal Health and Veterinary Laboratories Agency have discussed the need to recapture and rehome the population of wild beavers in Devon and also the process for doing so.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-06-26T10:28:33.0490001Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62900/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62900/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Beavers: Devon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with Natural England on the control of the population of wild beavers in Devon.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","201515"
