n","201222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62543","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>The engagement letter between the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills and the syndicate of banks involved in the initial public offering indicated that the payment of the discretionary fee would be determined 10 days after the end of the stabilisation period and paid 5 days after that.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As I said in my previous answer (1 May 2014, Official Report, column 782W), we informed the banks that a decision would not be taken in the timeframe set out in the engagement letter given the volatility of the Royal Mail share price after the IPO. The share price remains volatile.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have not set any timetable for the decision.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T14:00:07.4001238Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62543/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62543/answer","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62543/answer/previousversion/4736","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Answer of 1 May 2014, Official Report, column 782W, on Royal Mail, what link was established in the engagement letter between the payment of the discretionary fee and the ending of the stabilisation period; and what targets or deadlines were set in the letter.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","201166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62544","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-25","<p>The Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Bill will make provision for the implementation of a central registry of company beneficial ownership information. The legislation will set out the obligations and sanctions that will apply to companies and others to ensure that the central registry contains information on the ultimate owners and controllers of UK companies.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-25T14:53:05.9046456Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62544/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62544/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Companies: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the proposed beneficial ownership registry identifies the real controlling parties of all companies listed.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","201303"
