"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62557","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>The Illegal Money Lending Teams in England, Scotland and Wales receive intelligence via the helpline and also through via the “report a loan shark” web page on <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>, text messages, other electronic media and referrals from enforcement and debt advice agencies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Below is a breakdown of the number of calls received over the last four years and also the number of total pieces of intelligence received via all communications channels.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Telephone calls</strong></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Total Intelligence Received</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>370</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td> </td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>592</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>65</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>323</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td> </td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>657</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>117</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>214</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td> </td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>460</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>96</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Breakdown of number of calls received unavailable</p></td><td> </td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p>299</p></td><td><p>48</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Trading Standards is a devolved matter in Northern Ireland and so it is not possible to provide comparable data for there.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-23T16:48:57.3922065Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62557/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62557/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Illegal Money Lending Teams: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many telephone calls the Illegal Money Lending Unit helpline received from (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","201228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62558","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p><strong>Final Approved answer to 13371</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Illegal Money Lending Teams conduct complex and sensitive investigations. The length of each investigation will be influenced by the circumstances of the specific case. In some instances convictions can only be delivered through months of proactive intelligence gathering and community engagement. Because of this, some cases span across multiple years and so there is not necessarily a direct link between the numbers of actionable reports and the numbers of convictions in any one year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Below is a breakdown of the number of operations, arrests and prosecutions completed by the Illegal Money Lending Teams in England, Scotland and Wales in each of the last four years and the number of custodial sentences handed down by the courts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Operations</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Arrests / Detainments</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Prosecutions</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Custodials</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>74</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>107</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>55</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>73</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>92</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>34</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>57</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010/11*</strong></p></td><td><p>288</p></td><td><p>46</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>104</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>* The England Illegal Money Lending Team was restructured in April 2011- 9 England regional teams were merged into a single National team covering the whole of England.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-23T16:47:44.0059813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62558/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62558/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Money Lenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Answer of 14 May 2014, Official Report, column 678W, on money lenders, how many actionable reports led to a conviction in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","201229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62559","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-25","<p><strong>The Government is currently analysing the responses to the consultation on bail-in secondary legislation. Once this review is completed, the Government will publish a summary of the responses and indicate how it plans to proceed.</strong></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-25T13:48:01.6284472Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62559/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62559/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Building Societies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects to publish the results of the consultations on bail-in order for building societies; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","201186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62560","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>In 2010 this Government committed to ensuring the effective implementation of EU legislation so that British businesses are not put at a disadvantage relative to their European competitors.</p><p> </p><p>This Department follows the Government's Guiding Principles for EU legislation, which can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/185626/bis-13-774-guiding-principles-for-eu-legislation.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/185626/bis-13-774-guiding-principles-for-eu-legislation.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury is committed to ensuring that no unnecessary legislative burdens are placed on UK businesses when transposing EU law.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-23T14:57:43.5583816Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62560/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62560/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Delegated Legislation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department takes to ensure that delegated legislation brought forward by his Department is consistent with EU Directives.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","201212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62561","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>Estimates for the number of taxpayers in Northern Ireland with income from employment are published in HMRC's National Statistics Table 3.11 which is available at the following internet address for 2010/11 to 2011/12:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-and-tax-by-gender-region-and-country-2010-to-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-and-tax-by-gender-region-and-country-2010-to-2011</a></p><p> </p><p>Table 3.11 for 2009/10 and earlier can be found in the internet address below from the National Archives website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120609145917/http:/hmrc.gov.uk/stats/income_distribution/menu-by-year.htm#311" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120609145917/http://hmrc.gov.uk/stats/income_distribution/menu-by-year.htm#311</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the Survey of Personal Incomes for which 2011-12 is the latest year available. Figures for 2008/09 are not currently available.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-23T15:27:15.1712259Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62561/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62561/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Income Tax: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what change there was in the numbers of taxpayers in Northern Ireland who had employment income in the last four years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","201211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62562","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>'Managing Public Money', is published by HM Treasury and provides advice and guidance to central government on the use of public funds. It confirms that public sector organisations should not engage in tax evasion, or tax avoidance.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-23T15:07:48.5200214Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62562/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62562/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy that public sector organisations should not be allowed to be associated with tax avoidance schemes.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","201172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62563","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs has published extensive guidance to help employers run successful childcare schemes, including the Employer Helpbook E18 ‘How you can help your employees with childcare'.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-23T14:51:38.0247123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62563/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62563/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what guidance he has given on the role of employers in supporting the uptake and delivery of employer-supported childcare.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","201173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62564","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p><strong>On the 23 May the Government published a further consultation on the delivery of childcare accounts within Tax-Free Childcare. The consultation will be open until 27 June and the Government will consider the responses alongside those to the first consultation before it makes its decision on the provision of childcare accounts.</strong></p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-23T14:59:39.3457008Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62564/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62564/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62564/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that childcare providers receive payments from National Savings and Investments on time.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","201174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62565","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p><strong>Information on burdens for childcare providers associated with the introduction of Tax-Free Childcare can be found in the Impact Assessment: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/318698/document2014-06-10-104244-1.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/318698/document2014-06-10-104244-1.pdf</a></strong></p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-23T14:53:13.2550213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62565/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62565/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what additional burdens the impact assessment identified for childcare providers operating tax-free childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","201210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62566","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>The bank levy, a permanent tax on banks' balance sheet equity and liabilities, was introduced by this Government from 1 January 2011.</p><p> </p><p>It raised £1.6bn in both 2011-12 and 2012-13.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following a number of increases to the headline rate, the OBR now forecast it to raise £2.3bn in 2013-14, £2.7bn in 2014-15 and £2.9bn a year from 2015-16.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-23T15:42:42.1586223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62566/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62566/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Bank Levy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what revenues have been received under the bank levy in each year since its introduction.","false","Biography information for Duncan Hames","Chippenham","Duncan Hames","201157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62567","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p><strong>HM Treasury do not use 0845, 0844 or 0830 telephone numbers.</strong></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-23T15:16:08.3507948Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62567/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62567/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62567/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many telephone lines with the prefix (a) 0845, (b) 0844 and (c) 0843 his Department (i) operates and (ii) sponsors; how many calls each such number has received in the last 12 months; and whether alternative numbers charged at BT local rates are available in each such case.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","201390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62568","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-25","<p>Crowdfunding and peer to peer lending are innovative new forms of finance that support competition in the business lending sector.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has taken a number of steps to support their growth, including bringing peer to peer lending within the scope of the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), and announcing that the range of products that can be held in stocks and shares ISAs will be expanded to include loans made through peer to peer platforms.</p><p> </p><p>The Government also operates two tax-advantaged venture capital schemes which are used by equity crowdfunding investors; the Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme (SEIS) and the Enterprise Investment Scheme (EIS).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government has not made any assessment of the value of investment in small and medium sized businesses from peer to peer lending and crowdfunding platforms.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-25T13:54:48.657919Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62568/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62568/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62568/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Small Businesses: Crowdfunding","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 11 June 2014, Official Report, column 160W, on venture capital, what steps he has taken to support crowdfunding and peer-to-peer (a) lending to and (b) investment in small businesses; and if he will assess the value of such forms of finance to the small and medium-size sector.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","201391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62569","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-25","<p>Final figures for the Government spend on National Minimum Wage enforcement during 2013/14 are not yet available.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-25T14:39:07.4894122Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62569/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62569/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62569/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much the Government spent on National Minimum Wage enforcement in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","201395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62570","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>The National Minimum Wage enforcement budgets for 2013/14, 2014/15 and 2015/16 in principal were set out in Parliamentary Question 174284 on 7 November 2013, Official Report 7 Nov 2013, Col 351W.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The 2014/15 budget was reviewed at the start of the financial year and will be considered again at mid-year and may be subject to change.</p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-23T16:50:18.5222978Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62570/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62570/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62570/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-18","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the budget for enforcement of the National Minimum Wage was in 2013-14; and what that budget will be in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","201385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62571","HM Treasury","false","2014-08-05","<p>The data (the Office for Budget Responsibility’s forecast for debt in 2015-16 and HM Treasury projections for debt in 2035-36 under different policy assumptions with and without illustrative shocks) has been placed in the Library of the House. The forecast and projections have been provided both as a percentage of GDP and in £million in today’s terms.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-08-05T13:19:54.0081738Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62571/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62571/answer","chart b5 budget red book.doc","chart b5 budget red book.doc","chart B5, page 97 of the Budget 2014 Red Book","chart B5, page 97 of the Budget 2014 Red Book","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62571/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will place in the Library the underlying data to Chart B.5 on page 97 of the Budget 2014 Red Book in (a) percentage of gross domestic product and (b) £ million.","false","Biography information for James Duddridge","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","201381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62572","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>Previous replies have explained that further discussions in relation to the land at Priory Court in Dover are a matter for Mapeley who own the land. While HMRC occupy the property under the STEPS contract and will consider any reasonable proposals, resolution of commercial considerations are for Network Rail and Mapeley.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-23T15:30:12.0994496Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62572/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62572/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62572/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Dover Priory Station","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how long he expects discussions to be ongoing between Mapeley, Network Rail and HM Revenue and Customs on the sale of land on the western perimeter of the Priory Court site and the construction of new parking facilities for Dover Priory railway station.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","201340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62573","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-25","<p>The Government does not collect data on the number of applications made under the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Government publishes quarterly official statistics relating to the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme. The first of these were published on 29 May 2014.</p><p> </p><p>This report, along with accompanying tables, can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>The Help to Buy: equity loan scheme is a shared equity scheme. At Budget 2014, the Government announced that it will seek to explore how it can make the Help to Buy: equity loan scheme available for custom build.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the legal completions supported by the equity loan scheme are published monthly at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-25T14:06:17.0583974Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62573/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62573/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62573/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Help to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many applications for the Help to Buy scheme have been for (a) shared equity, (b) shared ownership, (c) mutual housing and (d) self-build properties since the scheme was launched.","false","Biography information for Andrew George","St Ives","Andrew George","201366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62574","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-23","<p>The Government publishes quarterly official statistics relating to the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme. The first of these were published on 29 May 2014.</p><p> </p><p>This report, along with accompanying tables, can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government has also recently published statistics on the completions supported by the Help to Buy: equity loan scheme. Full statistics covering the period April 2013 to March 2014 have been published as well as the number of completions, by local authority, to April 2014:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under both the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee and the Help to Buy: equity loan schemes borrowers need to declare that the property will be their sole residence.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-23T16:05:22.0921558Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62574/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62574/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62574/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Help to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many applications for the Help to Buy scheme have been received in respect of Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly from applicants who (a) reside in Cornwall and the Isle of Scilly and (b) do not reside in either place.","false","Biography information for Andrew George","St Ives","Andrew George","201367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62575","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-24","<p>Commercial arrangements in relation to the land at the Priory Court site are a matter for discussion between Network Rail and Mapeley. The Crown does not own the land.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-24T16:47:03.4790445Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62575/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62575/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62575/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Dover Priory Station","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, for what reasons Mapeley has not come to an agreement with Network Rail regarding the sale of land on the western perimeter of the Priory Court site for the construction of new parking facilities for Dover Priory railway station.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","201325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62576","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-24","<p>This government appreciates that times are tough and budgets are squeezed for families, which is why we have taken continued action to help ease the burden on hard working families.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Measures have included raising the Personal Allowance to £10500; abolishing the previous government's fuel duty escalator, and introducing a further 2 years of Council Tax freeze funding in 2014/15 and 2015/16 for local authorities which choose to freeze Council Tax.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","904409","2014-06-24T16:22:09.9010131Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62576/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62576/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62576/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-18","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what fiscal measures he has introduced to reduce the level of taxes paid by families.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","201312"
