"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62621","Department for Education","false","2014-06-23","<p>We have published guidance which sets out how publicly funded land and school playing fields are protected. This guidance is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-school-playing-fields-and-public-land-advice</a></p><p> </p><p>If land ceases, or will cease, to be used for an academy, the Secretary of State may need to make a determination in order to protect the public investment in the land. The Secretary of State will consider a range of factors including:</p><p>1. the degree of public investment in the land and the degree of any enhancement to the value attributable to that investment;</p><p>2. the degree of private investment in the land and the degree of any enhancement to the value attributable to that investment;</p><p>3. the length of time that the land has been in public use;</p><p>4. the value of the land at the date of determination.</p><p> </p><p>Information about the number of academies where land has been transferred from a governing body to an academy trust is not held centrally and could be compiled only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","201165 ; 201167 ; 201252 ; 201253","2014-06-23T15:51:41.7882788Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62621/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62621/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-18","Academies: Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, in what circumstances he would terminate a leasehold agreement with an academy trust prior to the expiration of a 125-year agreement.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","201254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62622","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-23","<p>I have not made such an estimate. However, we expect the impact of ground-source heat pump (GSHP) deployment on gas imports to be negligible.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-23T16:30:14.6198328Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62622/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62622/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Natural Gas: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if he will estimate the potential reduction in gas imports from the roll-out of ground sourced heat pumps.","false","Biography information for Roger Williams","Brecon and Radnorshire","Roger Williams","201247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62623","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Energy Performance Certificates can now be generated for park homes and the Energy Company Obligation is leading to improvements. For example, 200 park homes have had solid wall insulation under this scheme..</p><p>We will be consulting later this year on ways in which we could help park home rersidents access the Warm Home Discount.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:51:42.071124Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62623/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62623/answer","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62623/answer/previousversion/4699","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Mobile Homes: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if he will take steps to make consumer policies for energy more accessible to park home residents.","false","Biography information for Annette Brooke","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Annette Brooke","201240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62624","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>DECC's most recent projections of future electricity generation were made as part of the EMR December Delivery Plan 2013. The percentage of total electricity generation expected from nuclear sources in each calendar year is shown below in Table 1.</p><p>Table 1: Yearly percentage of total electricity generation expected from nuclear sources</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Percentage of total generation from nuclear sources (%)</strong></p></td><td><p>17.4%</p></td><td><p>17.6%</p></td><td><p>17.2%</p></td><td><p>17.3%</p></td><td><p>17.4%</p></td><td><p>17.4%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:57:46.7171827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62624/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62624/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of the UK's energy supply he expects to be obtained from nuclear energy in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Gareth Johnson","Dartford","Gareth Johnson","201221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62625","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Any sale of all or part of the UK Coal Group of companies would be a matter for the relevant board / boards of directors to consider and decide upon.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T15:45:59.8404545Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62625/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62625/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Coal: Mining","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether UK Coal Surface Mining is a limited company wholly owned by UK Coal Mining Holdings; and whether it can be sold off as a separate entity without the £20 million loan package being agreed between all parties.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","201216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62626","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change has not funded any co-sponsored research with US, French and German counterparts, at the US Sandia National Laboratories into the safety and security of spent nuclear fuel casks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-26T15:14:46.575713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62626/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62626/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Radioactive Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what research his Department has co-sponsored with its US, French and German counterparts at the Sandia National Laboratory into the safety and security of spent nuclear fuel casks; and if he will publish details of the reports arising from such research.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","201317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62627","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>On 17 June 2014, the UK signed two agreements relating to civil nuclear energy at the UK-China Summit. Both the Joint Statement on Civil Nuclear Energy Co-operation and the Memorandum of Understanding on Enhancing Co-operation in the Field of Civil Nuclear Industry Fuel Cycle Supply Chain are on the gov.uk website and can be viewed via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/multimillion-boost-to-uk-economy-as-china-and-uk-government-sign-civil-nuclear-agreement-and-sign-agreement-to-deepen-cooperation-on-climate-change" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/multimillion-boost-to-uk-economy-as-china-and-uk-government-sign-civil-nuclear-agreement-and-sign-agreement-to-deepen-cooperation-on-climate-change</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:58:18.0863537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62627/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62627/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Energy: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what commitments to transparency were included in the bilateral co-operation agreements with China on Energy announced on 17 June 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","201315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62628","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>From April 12th-15th, three officials from the Office for Nuclear Development visited Beijing to discuss the Joint Statement on Civil Nuclear Energy Co-operation and Memorandum of Understanding on Enhanced Co-operation on Civil Nuclear Industry Fuel Cycle Supply Chain with the Chinese Government. Officials also attended various other meetings to understand Chinese civil nuclear capability and to explain UK regulatory requirements. The cost of this visit was £11, 787.38.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:56:25.2040336Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62628/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62628/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Energy: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the cost has been of the visit of his Department's officials ahead of the completion of the agreements on energy collaboration with China signed on 17 June 2014; and if he will publish the dates and purpose of each such visit.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","201316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62629","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The net DEL figure for 2014/15 is £2,298.7m.</p><p> </p><p><em>Source: DECC 2014-15 Main Estimate Explanatory Memorandum</em></p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T14:50:09.4509168Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62629/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62629/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Nuclear power: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what funds have been provided from his departmental expenditure limit for nuclear decommissioning in the 2014-15 financial year.","false","Biography information for Geraint Davies","Swansea West","Geraint Davies","201346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62630","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Data is not available to the Department on the number of households with prepayment meters at the parliamentary constituency or local authority level.</p><p>Statistics are produced on a quarterly basis which show the proportion of households on prepayment tariffs by Public Electricity Supply (PES) region. These are made available through the DECC publication Quarterly Energy Prices, in tables 242 (electricity) and 252 (gas), which can be found online at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/quarterly-domestic-energy-price-stastics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/quarterly-domestic-energy-price-stastics</a></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:50:32.3724505Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62630/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62630/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the number of households with prepayment meters in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority in each year between 1996 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","201361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62631","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The estimated number and proportion of households which are fuel poor for 2011 and 2012 under the Low Income High Costs (LIHC) Indicator in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fuel-poverty-sub-regional-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fuel-poverty-sub-regional-statistics</a></p><p>The link above also provides sub-regional estimates of fuel poverty for the 10% indicator for the years 2010, 2011 and 2012. Estimates for 2006, 2008 and 2009 under the 10% indicator are available from the fuel poverty statistics archive page:</p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130109092117/http:/decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/statistics/fuelpov_stats/archive/archive.aspx" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130109092117/http:/decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/statistics/fuelpov_stats/archive/archive.aspx</a></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","201399","2014-06-24T15:53:50.5861483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62631/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62631/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what forecast his Department has made of the number of households in fuel poverty in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority in (i) 2013 and (ii) 2014.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","201362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62632","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The estimated number and proportion of households which are fuel poor for 2011 and 2012 under the Low Income High Costs (LIHC) Indicator in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fuel-poverty-sub-regional-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fuel-poverty-sub-regional-statistics</a></p><p>The link above also provides sub-regional estimates of fuel poverty for the 10% indicator for the years 2010, 2011 and 2012. Estimates for 2006, 2008 and 2009 under the 10% indicator are available from the fuel poverty statistics archive page:</p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130109092117/http:/decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/statistics/fuelpov_stats/archive/archive.aspx" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130109092117/http:/decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/statistics/fuelpov_stats/archive/archive.aspx</a></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","201362","2014-06-24T15:53:50.4923618Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62632/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62632/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-18","Fuel Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate his Department has made of the number of households in fuel poverty in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority in each year between 1996 and 2012.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","201399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62634","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>As part of schemes funded through Local Levy and Flood Defence Grant-in-Aid, work to protect ten properties in the Mudeford and Stanpit area is planned for 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Property-level protection measures were installed at twelve properties in Stony Lane, Christchurch earlier this year.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-23T11:07:45.6241769Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62634/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62634/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-18","Floods: Christchurch","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he expects work to all properties identified by the Environment Agency in Christchurch constituency as being suitable for Property Level Protection against flooding to be completed.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","201380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62635","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-23","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer that I gave to the hon. Member for Bristol East (Kerry McCarthy), on 17 June 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 516W.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-23T11:23:07.9619231Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62635/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62635/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-18","Forests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress his Department has made on placing the public forest estate on a sustainable footing; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","201377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62636","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>The “Repair and Renew” grant is available to establish resilience and resistance measures in properties to minimise the risk of damage caused by flooding. As it stands, the grant only applies to homes and businesses affected by flooding and excludes non-habitable areas.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-23T13:59:20.6500721Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62636/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62636/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-18","Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether garages, boiler rooms and other non-habitable areas affected by flooding are eligible for the Repair and Renew Grant.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","201376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62637","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-23","<p>As of 19 June, no such representations have been received from environmental groups.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-06-23T10:25:14.0439329Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62637/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62637/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-18","Beef: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what representations he has received from environmental groups regarding beef consumption and the countries from which the UK imports beef.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","201345"
