"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62746","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>We announced our plans for the implementation of Universal Credit on 5 December, and these were set out in a written ministerial statement <em>Official Report </em><em>5 Dec 2013</em><em>, Column 65WS</em>. The WMS can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm131205/wmstext/131205m0001.htm#13120551000006" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201314/cmhansrd/cm131205/wmstext/131205m0001.htm#13120551000006</a></p><p> </p><p>Official statistics on Universal Credit were most recently published on 14th May and can be found at</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>Our estimates of the number of appeals will depend on the details of the migration schedule which will be determined in due course.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-23T17:02:16.8182099Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62746/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62746/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-18","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has given to the tribunals service of how many appeals will be brought by universal credit claimants in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","201241"
